This paper proposes a method for grading cataract severity using retinal images, which involves feature extraction and classification. The paper uses a neural network for classification, which is a common technique in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature engineering and classification, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.DL). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
